CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 14, 1953, pg. 23, reads: "Fun at Four Corners - Homestead was the fun mecca last week as the crowd converged on the popular Four Corners Tavern at Seventh and Ann Street. This cozy spot, operated by Jimmy Hill and Clarence Lampkin, is growing in minds of the people as 'the place to go.'"
TitMainTitle: Men, and women, including one on right with Persian lamb coat over shoulders, gathered around tables in Four Corners Tavern, Homestead
